	In article <1993Jan29.223411.6962@fuug.fi> an8729@anon.penet.fi writes:
	[suggesting that workstations are getting fast enough to be able to use
	raw RSA for encryption (cites 2 mintues for a 2K binary file using a 1K key)]

	1.	2 minutes is too long to wait for decryption.  RIPEM with a
		key of 1024 bits takes about 7 seconds to do a decryption on
		my Sparcstation 1 and that's long enough to be annoying.

It depends why you're doing it.  If you have something that you don't want
people who can afford a DES-cruncher to read, surely the inconvenience of
a few minutes decrypt time shouldn't bother you?  I'd be *much* happier
with RSA encryption on private mail.  It's never very big anyway...

